description.narrative: This strategy aims at supporting countries to strengthen and optimize key supply chains with governments for targeted products and locations to reduce costs, stock-outs and/or wastage, improve performance and help achieve results for children.In 2021, 6 countries increased their maturity level in at least one area of the supply chain.From 2018 to 2021, the indicator target was met with 15 countries increasing at least one level of their supply chain maturity: Burkina Faso, Cote d&39;Ivoire, Democratic Republic of Congo, Ethiopia, Liberia, Malawi, Mali, Mauritania, Niger, Nigeria, Pakistan, Papua New Guinea Senegal, Sierra Leone and Uzbekistan | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/03/2022
